Title: The Bogoluibov Renormalization Group in Theoretical and Mathematical

PhysicsComments: 20 pages, LaTeX

This text follows the line of a talk on Ringberg symposium dedicated toWolfhart Zimmermann 70th birthday. The historical overview (Part 1) partiallyoverlaps with corresponding text of my previous commemorative paper. At thesame time second part includes some recent results in QFT and summarize animpressive progress of the "QFT renormalization group" application inmathematical physics.